<br>
What flaws in the game mechanics do you think should be fixed in order to make EQ a better game.<br>
<br>
My first idea is truly random spawn times.  I mean random spawn from server ups and after death.  It needs to be a wide window too.  So all players around the world can have an equal chance at all mobs.  After server comes up no highly contested raid type mob should be up, the mob should have a window of 24 or 48 hours,  It can spawn.  This means it can spawn at server ups but it can also spawn several several hours after servers come up.  This would be the same for after the mob dies.<br>
<br>
My other idea would be some type of system, either monitoring or priority petition system.  It is a known fact that competition is blood thirsty, some guild will do anything and everything to get a mob and with the new petition system its impossible to do anything about it.  I propose either a system that is set in place that becomes active whenever a named mob spawns.  It will monitor and record all players action until the said named mob is dead.  Not sure if its codeable but this way Verant will have the evidence they need on their system.  Since almost any evidence the players can provide other then report is considered unusable.<br>
<br>
The other solution could be some sort of priority petition system.  That when a priority petition is made if the guide/gm reading said petition doesn't deem it an immediate action item will delete it and continue with their work.  Make the petition like a report, only able to have one per zone.  Players who abuse it will be reprimanded.  VI would have to set what type of petitions should be considered immediate action and create a box that you have to choose yes or no that you are aware of making petitions that aren't considered immediate response petitions then you can and will be reprimanded.<br>
<br>
Well that is my ideas.  Civil conversations only about any ideas posted here if any.  I just want to get an idea of what the players considered a priority of what should be fixed/changed.<br>
<br>
